  "response": "In 2016, Harris Corporation (now L3Harris Technologies after merging with L3 Technologies in 2019) focused on several key areas. Here's a breakdown of some of their most interesting products and innovations that year, keeping in mind information from that time period:\n\n**Focus Areas:**\n\n*   **Advanced Communications:** Harris was a leader in secure communication systems.\n*   **Electronic Warfare:** They provided solutions for electronic warfare, signal intelligence, and cyber defense.\n*   **Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR):** Harris developed systems for gathering and processing intelligence data.\n*   **Space and Weather:** They were involved in space-based systems for communication, weather forecasting, and remote sensing.\n\n**Specific Products and Innovations (Based on information available from 2016):**\n\n*   **Falcon III\u00ae Radios:** Harris continued to advance its Falcon III line of radios. These were key for tactical communication and provided enhanced capabilities in terms of range, security, and data transmission. Specific models and upgrades likely included:\n    *   **AN/PRC-117G:** This radio was a major product for secure wideband communication. Innovations in 2016 would have focused on improving its network capabilities and reducing its size and weight.\n    *   **AN/PRC-152A:** This is a handheld multiband radio, that provided voice and data services, so further development would have seen improved security, range and power efficiencies.\n*   **Electronic Warfare Systems:** They worked on advanced jammers, signal interceptors, and cyber defense tools.\n*   **Geospatial Solutions:** Harris provided software and services for geospatial data processing and analysis.\n*   **Weather Satellites:** Harris developed instruments for weather satellites. In 2016, their contributions to the next-generation GOES-R satellite would have been significant.\n*   **Cybersecurity:** Harris was working on cybersecurity solutions for government and commercial customers, focusing on threat detection, prevention, and response.\n\n**Key Trends and Innovations:**\n\n*   **Software-Defined Radios (SDR):** Harris was a leader in SDR technology, which allowed radios to be reconfigured via software to support different waveforms and protocols. This was a major trend that allowed for greater flexibility and interoperability.\n*   **Cognitive Radio:** The company was exploring cognitive radio technologies that could adapt to changing RF environments and optimize communication performance.\n*   **Networked Communications:** Harris was focused on developing networked communication systems that could connect various devices and platforms seamlessly.\n*   **Cybersecurity Integration:** Integrating cybersecurity into all of its products and systems was a major priority for Harris.\n*   **Smaller, Lighter, More Power-Efficient:** A consistent theme across all their product lines was the drive to create smaller, lighter, and more power-efficient devices. This was particularly important for tactical radios and other portable equipment.\n\n**Please note:**\n\n*   L3Harris Technologies was formed through a merger in 2019. Information related to specific product lines of Harris prior to the merger might now be integrated or rebranded within L3Harris.\n\nTo get more precise details on specific products released in 2016, I'd recommend searching for press releases, news articles, and product announcements from Harris Corporation from that year. You might also find information on defense industry websites and publications.",
